Package: intraclass
Title: Modern Intraclass Correlation Coefficients
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R:
    person("Jeffrey", "Girard", , "jeffgirard@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-7359-3746"))
Description: Estimates interrater-reliability intraclass correlation
    coefficients (ICCs) within the generalizability-theory framework using
    modern variance-component estimation (linear mixed models) rather than
    the classical ANOVA mean-squares approach. Provides the full ICC family
    (absolute agreement versus consistency, single versus average, fixed
    versus random raters) with boundary-aware Monte-Carlo confidence
    intervals, support for imbalanced and incomplete designs, and guidance
    on choosing the correct coefficient.
